    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A type of rectangular gem cut in which the corners are cut off. Mainly used for emeralds, but can also be used for other gemstones and diamonds. In comparison to a baguette cut, the emerald cut has more horizontally broken facets and also facets in the corners.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
